<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1615,2002]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,152,498]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,312,1695,1721]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Remarks</emphasis>
. The taxonomic position of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kossmann" authorityYear="1879" box="[647,783,1696,1721]" class="Malacostraca" family="Progeryonidae" genus="Paragalene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[647,783,1696,1721]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Paragalene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has always been unclear. Some authors affiliate it with the 
<taxonomicName box="[194,314,1736,1762]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Xanthidae</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nardo, G. D." box="[381,523,1736,1762]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" pagination="217 - 343" refId="ref7751" refString="Nardo, G. D. (1868) Annotazioni illustranti cinquantaquattro specie di Crostacei podottalmi, endottalmi e succhiatori del mare Adriatico, alcune delle quali nuove o male conosciute, accompagnate da trentare figure litografate, e precedute dalla storia della carcinologia Adriatica antica e rencente. Memorie del Reale Istituto Veneto di Scienze Lettere e Arti, Venezia, 14 (2), 217 - 343, pls. 12 - 15." type="journal article" year="1868">Nardo 1868</bibRefCitation>
; d’Udekem 
<bibRefCitation author="Udekem d'Acoz, C. d'" box="[665,819,1736,1762]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" refId="ref8397" refString="Udekem d'Acoz, C. d' (1999) Inventaire des Crustaces Decapodes de l'Atlantique nord-oriental, de la Mediterranee et des eaux continentales adjacentes au nord de 25 ° N. Museum national d'Histoire naturelle / Service du Patrimoine Naturel, Collection Patrimoines Naturels, Paris, 40, 383 pp." type="book" year="1999">d’Acoz 1999</bibRefCitation>
) while others provisionally align it with the 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Geryonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Geryonidae</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Turkay, M." box="[266,432,1776,1802]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" pagination="57 - 74" refId="ref8289" refString="Turkay, M. (1976 a) Die Madeirensischen Brachyuren des Museu Municipal do Funchal und des Forscungs-Instituts Senckenberg. I. Familien: Dromiidae, Homolidae, Calappidae, Leucosiidae, cancridae, Portunidae, Xanthidae, Geryonidae, Goneplacidae und Palicidae (Crustacea: Decapoda). Boletin du Museu Municipal do Funchal, 30 (133), 57 - 74, pls. 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="1976">Türkay 1976a</bibRefCitation>
, b). 
<bibRefCitation author="Manning, R. B. &amp; Holthuis, L. B." box="[484,813,1776,1802]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" pagination="50 - 77" refId="ref7700" refString="Manning, R. B. &amp; Holthuis, L. B. (1989) Two new genera and nine new species of geryonid crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda: Geryonidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 102 (1), 50 - 77." type="journal article" year="1989">Manning &amp; Holthuis (1989)</bibRefCitation>
did not agree that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kossmann" authorityYear="1879" box="[1032,1169,1776,1801]" class="Malacostraca" family="Progeryonidae" genus="Paragalene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1032,1169,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Paragalene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bouvier" authorityYear="1922" box="[1226,1350,1776,1801]" class="Malacostraca" family="Progeryonidae" genus="Progeryon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1226,1350,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Progeryon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be placed in the 
<taxonomicName box="[352,488,1816,1842]" class="Malacostraca" family="Geryonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Geryonidae</taxonomicName>
and suggested that a new family may need to be established for them. 
<bibRefCitation author="Stevcic, Z." pageId="9" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 159" refId="ref8257" refString="Stevcic, Z. (2005) The reclassification of Brachyuran Crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura). Fauna Croatica, 14 (1), 1 - 159." type="journal article" year="2005">Števčić (2005: 64)</bibRefCitation>
, however, placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kossmann" authorityYear="1879" box="[486,623,1856,1881]" class="Malacostraca" family="Progeryonidae" genus="Paragalene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[486,623,1856,1881]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Paragalene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a new tribe, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stevcic, 2005" authorityName="Stevcic" authorityYear="2005" box="[804,1121,1855,1882]" class="Malacostraca" family="Progeryonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Paragalenini">
Paragalenini 
<bibRefCitation author="Stevcic, Z." box="[958,1121,1855,1882]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 159" refId="ref8257" refString="Stevcic, Z. (2005) The reclassification of Brachyuran Crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura). Fauna Croatica, 14 (1), 1 - 159." type="journal article" year="2005">Števčić, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Colosi" authorityYear="1923" class="Malacostraca" family="Geryonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Geryoninae">Geryoninae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[208,344,1896,1922]" class="Malacostraca" family="Geryonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Geryonidae</taxonomicName>
(without any comment as usual). Karasawa &amp; Schweitzer (2005) discussed the affinities of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kossmann" authorityYear="1879" box="[151,288,1936,1961]" class="Malacostraca" family="Progeryonidae" genus="Paragalene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,288,1936,1961]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Paragalene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bouvier" authorityYear="1922" box="[357,481,1936,1961]" class="Malacostraca" family="Progeryonidae" genus="Progeryon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[357,481,1936,1961]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Progeryon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but while they recognised the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stevcic" authorityYear="2005" box="[941,1115,1936,1962]" class="Malacostraca" family="Progeryonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Progeryonidae</taxonomicName>
, they postponed a decision on the position of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kossmann" authorityYear="1879" box="[365,501,1976,2001]" class="Malacostraca" family="Progeryonidae" genus="Paragalene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[365,501,1976,2001]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Paragalene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Manuel-Santos, M. R." box="[517,898,1976,2002]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" pagination="39 - 68" refId="ref7919" refString="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Manuel-Santos, M. R. (2007) Establishment of the Vultocinidae, a new family for an unusual new genus and new species of Indo-West Pacific crab (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Goneplacoidea), with comments on the taxonomy of the Goneplacidae. Zootaxa, 1558, 39 - 68." type="journal article" year="2007">Ng &amp; Manuel-Santos (2007: 44)</bibRefCitation>
provisionally left it in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stevcic" authorityYear="2005" box="[1213,1386,1976,2002]" class="Malacostraca" family="Progeryonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Progeryonidae</taxonomicName>
, but in an addendum 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Manuel-Santos, M. R." box="[343,722,152,178]" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" pagination="39 - 68" refId="ref7919" refString="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Manuel-Santos, M. R. (2007) Establishment of the Vultocinidae, a new family for an unusual new genus and new species of Indo-West Pacific crab (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Goneplacoidea), with comments on the taxonomy of the Goneplacidae. Zootaxa, 1558, 39 - 68." type="journal article" year="2007">Ng &amp; Manuel-Santos (2007: 55)</bibRefCitation>
briefly confirmed this when they examined specimens. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Guinot, D. &amp; Davie, P. J. F." pageId="10" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 286" refId="ref7984" refString="Ng, P. K. L., Guinot, D. &amp; Davie, P. J. F. (2008). Systema Brachyurorum: Part 1. An annotated checklist of extant Brachyuran crabs of the world. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement 17, 1 - 286." type="journal article" year="2008">
Ng 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="63">et al.</emphasis>
(2008: 84)
</bibRefCitation>
also briefly commented on the status of this genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,152,498]" pageId="10" pageNumber="63">
The carapace of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kossmann" authorityYear="1879" box="[395,532,232,257]" class="Malacostraca" family="Progeryonidae" genus="Paragalene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[395,532,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="63">Paragalene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bouvier" authorityYear="1922" box="[689,813,232,257]" class="Malacostraca" family="Progeryonidae" genus="Progeryon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[689,813,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="63">Progeryon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the strong transverse gastric and branchial ridges on the carapace, and the sharp, prominent anterolateral teeth. The first 
<specimenCount box="[985,1108,272,298]" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" type="male">three male</specimenCount>
abdominal somites are also proportionally narrower transversely, with somites 3 and 4 fused rather than free. These differences are important at the generic but not at the family level. The condition of the male thoracic sternum, position of the press button of the male abdominal locking mechanism, structure of the male abdomen and form of the male gonopods, however, all agree very well with those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bouvier" authorityYear="1922" box="[714,838,432,457]" class="Malacostraca" family="Progeryonidae" genus="Progeryon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[714,838,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="63">Progeryon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and we have little doubt that it should be placed in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stevcic" authorityYear="2005" box="[194,365,472,498]" class="Malacostraca" family="Progeryonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Progeryonidae</taxonomicName>
as defined here.
</paragraph>
